**Lambda, Map, Filter & Reduce**
--> These tools help you write compact, efficient and data-friendly code 
--> is perfect for data science and automation
1) Lambda Functions (Anonymous Functions);
--> it is a small one-line function without a name
syntax:- lambda arguments: expression
2) map() Function;
--> map() applies a function to each element in a list (or any iterable)
ex:- nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
     squares = list(map(lambda x: x ** 2, nums))
     print(squares)
3) filter() Function;
--> filter() selects items based on a condition (True/False)
ex:- nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]
     even_nums = list(filter(lambda x: x % 2 == 0, nums))
     print(even_nums)
4) reduce() Function;
--> applies a function cumulatively to the list, combining all elements into one result
--> You must import it from functools
ex:- from functools import reduce
     nums = [1, 2, 3, 4]
     product = reduce(lambda a, b: a * b, nums)
     print(product)
====> to combine above all in one code<==== ;
from functools import reduce
nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]
doubles = list(map(lambda x: x * 2, nums))
filtered = list(filter(lambda x: x > 6, doubles))
total = reduce(lambda a, b: a + b, filtered)
print("Doubles:", doubles)
print("Filtered (>6):", filtered)
print("Total:", total)
